Head of Telesales Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of rapidly growing multinational consumer goods company. Our respected client is seeking a sales professional with at least five years’ experience with a respectable consumer goods company, including three years in a managerial role, for the job of Head of Telesales, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. This job is only open to professional salespersons who are highly motivated to increase sales Key job responsibilities will include: Manages and drives performance of TeleSales teamDevelops and executes TeleSales planApplies local sales incentive schemes for TeleSales channel based on defined sales indexEnsures achievement of country sales index for TeleSales teamSteers and improves sales performance through effective processes and performance measurementPlans and manages portfolio of small business customersSupport TeleSales specialist in winning, retaining and developing Business Customers in SBC segmentActs as a coach for TeleSales Team  Requirements: Bachelor’s degree (minimum)Five years’ experience (minimum) in sales in forwarding industry with 3 years at managerial levelGood understanding of the forwarding industry and deep knowledge on DGF products (AFR/OFR) and business modelsWell-developed management skills and collaborative leadership style to steer sales teamAbility to take ownership and proactively address topicsGood communication, presentation and negotiation skillsAbility to win, develop and close new businessAbility to identify customer needs by gathering information and building long-term relationshipFluent in English verbal/written communication All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to consumer@monroeconsulting.com
